goals.question: What is the distribution of bird strikes by airport?
goals.rationale: This can help identify airports with high bird strike incidents and inform decisions on bird control measures.

goals.question: Which aircraft make and model has the highest number of bird strikes?
goals.rationale: This can help identify aircrafts that are more prone to bird strikes and inform decisions on aircraft design and maintenance.

goals.question: What is the distribution of bird strikes by wildlife species?
goals.rationale: This can help identify wildlife species that are more likely to cause bird strikes and inform decisions on wildlife management.

goals.question: What is the relationship between the speed of the aircraft and the amount of damage caused by the bird strike?
goals.visualization: scatter plot of Speed_IAS_in_knots vs Effect_Amount_of_damage
goals.rationale: This can help identify if there is a correlation between the speed of the aircraft and the amount of damage caused by the bird strike.

goals.question: What is the distribution of bird strikes by phase of flight?
goals.rationale: This can help identify the phase of flight when bird strikes are more likely to occur and inform decisions on flight operations.

import seaborn as sns
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    chart = sns.countplot(x='Airport_Name', data=data)
    plt.title('What is the distribution of bird strikes by airport?', wrap=True)
    plt.xticks(rotation=90)
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        chart.xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
plt.show()

import seaborn as sns
import statsmodels.api as sm
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    species_count = data['Wildlife_Species'].value_counts()
    chart = sns.barplot(x=species_count.index, y=species_count.values)
    plt.title('What is the distribution of bird strikes by wildlife species?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Wildlife Species')
    plt.ylabel('Number of Bird Strikes')
    
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        chart.xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    
    plt.xticks(rotation=90)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()

import seaborn as sns
import statsmodels.api as sm
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    sns.scatterplot(data=data, x='Speed_IAS_in_knots', y='Effect_Amount_of_damage')
    plt.title('What is the relationship between the speed of the aircraft and the amount of damage caused by the bird strike?', wrap=True)
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):

    plt.pie(phase_counts, labels=phase_counts.index, autopct='%1.1f%%')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of bird strikes by phase of flight?', wrap=True)

chart = plot(data)
